        "node_id":  "C_kwDOSVlrQ9oAKGQ4NGM2MGZmYjQ2MWE3OWVhN2UyNDM3ZDgzYmQ4YjVlODgyYTY3YWQ",
        "commit":  {
                       "author":  {
                                      "name":  "drhalilmurattasci",
                                      "email":  "drhalilmurattasci@users.noreply.github.com",
                                      "date":  "2026-06-05T13:23:42Z"
                                  },
                       "committer":  {
                                         "name":  "drhalilmurattasci",
                                         "email":  "drhalilmurattasci@users.noreply.github.com",
                                         "date":  "2026-06-05T13:23:42Z"
                                     },
                       "message":  "feat(dispatch): flight-ready guard -- live watch path + hardened source-tagged hard rules\n\nMake Invoke-AiDispatchGuard.ps1 able to actually supervise a live autonomous run\n(so Claude\u0027s watch/safety role is operational, not just a dry-run scaffold), and\napply the fixes from the Codex control review of #316.\n\nLive path (Invoke-GuardLiveRun, previously threw \"not armed\"):\n- launches the driver (-DriverCommand, default Invoke-AiDispatchAuto.ps1) as a\n  Start-Process child, redirecting stdout/stderr and tailing them incrementally\n  into watch.log + events.jsonl;\n- classifies each line by source (signal / command / prose) and tracks liveness\n  by output growth + process state;\n- assesses every -AssessIntervalSec via claude -p (fail-safe: unparseable =\u003e\n  abort); -MockAssess substitutes a scripted verdict for offline smoke tests;\n- on any abort kills the child process tree (taskkill /T /F) + writes\n  abort-report.md; exit 0 = completed, 2 = aborted.\n\nHard-rule fixes (Codex #316 control review):\n- #1/#2 broadened protected-ref + force-push detection (origin main, HEAD:main,\n  refs/heads/main, +main, URL remote; --force / -f / +refspec);\n- #3 source-tagged matching: command patterns match only command-classified text,\n  signal patterns only signal text, so prose that merely MENTIONS a dangerous\n  command can never trip a hard rule;\n- #4/#5 AUTONOMOUS_WATCH.md reconciled: live behaviors documented as built (not\n  overstated), and the false \"-DryRun is the default\" claim removed (it is a\n  switch; omitting it enters the live path).\n\nTwo Start-Process bugs found + fixed by the live smoke test: $proc.ExitCode came\nback null (cache $proc.Handle) and taskkill on an already-exited child trapped\nunder EAP=Stop (EAP-isolated). The same EAP isolation is applied to the claude call.\n\nValidation: live smoke (complete / signal-abort / command-abort) green; dry-run\n0/2/2; new Pester GuardSafetyMonitor.Tests.ps1 32/32 (locks in #1/#2/#3); full\ndispatch-tests 347/347; PSScriptAnalyzer (repo settings) 0 findings across all\ntracked ps1. PowerShell + Markdown only (no Rust); the canonical Rust gate is\nunaffected and covered by CI on clean runners. NOT armed: scheduler not\nregistered, guard not pointed at the real driver with -PublishMode main, no live\nrun.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
